{
  "texts": [
    "This means that in the tool selection process of each round, agents can naturally choose cooperative tools in the same way as common tools, allowing an agent to request assistance from other agents in some complex tasks.",
    "Meanwhile, cooperative tools include deactivation tool like Disconnect (agent list), which enables an agent to release collaborators if they are no longer needed.",
    "To facilitate this process, in Tool-RoCo, each agent maintains an active agent pool that records which agents are currently active and which are inactive.",
    "When an active tool of cooperative tools is used to connect an agent, the target agent is added to the pool; when a disconnect tool is invoked, the agent is removed.",
    "This pool allows each agent to manage dynamic collaboration efficiently and ensures that subsequent tool selections can take into account the current set of active collaborators."
  ]
}